  "texts": [
    "Locations with relative motion sufficient to break biological objects, which is consistent with motion of the same objects in preceding and following sections, and where the motion corresponds to small areas or naturally fast moving structures, such as axon bundles and tissue boundary, are classified as Natural Variation. 3.",
    "Locations with relative motion sufficient to break biological objects which is not consistent with motion of the same objects in the preceding and following sections are classified as Misalignment. 4.",
    "Locations with relative motion sufficient to break of biological objects which is consistentf which with motion of the same objects in preceding and following sections, and where the motion corresponds to a large area of not naturally fast moving structures are classified as Misalignments. 5.",
    "Locations that do not qualify for criteria 1-4 and contain visual artifacts such as contrast and brightness variation are classified as Visual Artifact. 6.",
    "Locations that do not qualify for criteria 1-5 are classified as Natural Variation."
  ],
